Police arrested a man for selling fake tickets ahead of the Absa Premiership match between Orlando Pirates and Free State Stars at Orlando Stadium on Saturday night.The Premier Soccer League (PSL) confirmed on Monday that the 41 year-old suspect from Snake Park in Doornkop Soweto was found in possession of 18 fraudulent match tickets.He has been charged with fraud and contravening Safety at Sports and Recreational events Act of 2010."We commend the work of the police who have been working very closely with us in curbing the illegal sale of tickets at our stadiums and the fraudulent activities by some individuals " PSL Head of Safety and Security Phillip Masimong said."As the League we are determined to put an end to this practice."But in order for us to be successful we obviously need the SAPS on board."Going forward we intend to intensify our efforts to put an end to the sale of fraudulent tickets at PSL Matches". - TMG Digital